post_text:
CHIP covers uninsured children and teens up to age 19 – and no family earns too much to qualify. With more than 124,000 uninsured children in Pennsylvania, this is great news for families!

CHIP provides quality, comprehensive health insurance for routine doctor visits, prescriptions, dental, eye care, eyeglasses, mental health, and much more. CHIP covers uninsured kids who are not eligible for Medical Assistance. For most families, CHIP is free – for others, it is low cost.

Free Meals for Children in the Summer

The Summer Food Service Program (SFSP) offers free, nutritious meals to children 18 years and younger during the summer when school is not in session.

SFSP is a federal child nutrition program. There are approximately 2500 locations throughout Pennsylvania that serve breakfast, lunch and /or snacks. Many of the locations provide activities as well.

How to find a SFSP location near you:
-- Call: 211 or 1.866.3HUNGRY or 1.877.8HAMBRE
-- Text: “FOOD” or “COMIDA” to 877877
-- Download: RangeAPP.org mobile app
-- Visit: fns.usda.gov/summerfoodrocks

shared_text:
York County Alliance for Learning - YCAL
June 9 at 12:00 PM ·

YCAL SENIOR SPOTLIGHT:

Congratulations to graduating Senior Ashley Coggins from South Western High School (South Western High School). Ashley took full advantage of the YCAL Career Exploration Programs, attending Healthcare, Medical Assistant, Psychology & Human Studies, Nursing, Respiratory Care, and Business Management during her high school years. "My favorite YCAL program was the nursing one (hosted by WellSpan Health's York Hospital) because it allowed me to experience the many different aspects of nursing. You can take nursing many different routes and I can’t wait to see where my journey takes me."

Future Plans: Attending York College of Pennsylvania to pursue a degree in Nursing.

Congratulations and good luck, to you!

post_text:
SWSD Volunteer ID Badge Return

Thank you to all district volunteers for your services to the South Western School District. Please return your volunteer photo ID badge to any of the district school building offices.

Beginning June 1, drop boxes will be available outside the main entrance of each district building during business hours. Please return your volunteer photo ID badge by June 30.

Volunteer status is valid for the current school year only. District volunteers must re-register each school year to remain on the district volunteer cleared list. Current clearances on file are valid for 60 months from the date completed, as long as the volunteer re-registers each school year. Volunteer ID badges will be returned at the time of renewal.

post_text:
HS Yearbook Update

Our Yearbook Company is finally back open as of today, May 18th. Unfortunately, due to the shut-down, the yearbook company now has to catch up on all of their printing for high schools and universities throughout the country. This means that our yearbooks will NOT be in by mid-June as we had hoped back in April. Our delivery date to the school is now set for between July 16th - July 21st.

As the date nears closer, we will receive updates from the company and then we will be able to make our distribution / extra sales plan with the admin team.

We know this is not the news you wanted to hear, but please know that we will be working on a plan to get the yearbook to you as soon as we can once they arrive in July.

Until then, we are taking names for anyone who wishes to purchase one of our extra yearbooks. We have about 30 left, so don't delay! You may email us at swhsequestrian@gmail.com to get your name on the list.

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this time.
Ms. Fritz, Ms. Danfelt, & The Equestrian Staff

post_text: This is an important message from the South Western School District. During the arrival of secondary students this morning, February 7th, the district was notified of a tornado warning by the National Weather Service. As a precaution, all district schools initiated their severe weather shelter-in-place procedures, and will remain in this status until the warning is lifted at 8:30 a.m. or until further information is received. We appreciate everyone's understanding and if any new information arises, we will communicate accordingly.

Manheim Elementary recently lost power to the building. We have learned the power will not be restored until approximately 1:00 or later. As a result of the cold temperatures and the lack of heated airflow, we are concerned about the temperature of the building falling over the next few hours. As a result of the power loss, the students will be receiving a bag lunch and will depart the building for our middle school within the hour.

Manheim students will be dismissing at their normal time from the middle school this afternoon. If you are planning to pick up your student from the middle school at dismissal, we are asking all parents to drive to the rear of the building. District staff will be on site to assist with traffic flow.

Thank you

Good Evening Parents/Guardians, the following is an important message from the South Western School District:

Late this afternoon an anonymous threat was discovered in one of the student restrooms at EHMIS. As a result of this discovery, the administration, along with the assistance of Penn Township Police, immediately investigated the threat and determined it was not credible. Additionally, it was also determined that at no time was any student or employee in danger. EHMIS will open tomorrow on time and operate on a normal schedule. We would once again like to thank Penn Township Police for their immediate response and assistance as we all work to keep our students and staff safe.

Thank you.

post_text:
South Western High School Third Annual Veterans Day Assembly
South Western High School, Hanover, PA - November 8, 2019

South Western High School will be holding its fifth annual Veterans Day Celebration on Friday, November 8th from 8:30 to 12:30. The morning will begin with a breakfast to thank our veterans along with the presentation of The Veteran Project. Following breakfast, we will be holding a school-wide assembly to honor all veterans with guest speak Lt. General Ralph Jodice. At the conclusion of the assembly participating veterans will be in a Living Museum in HS main lobby to share stories, experiences, and memorabilia. All veterans and active military are welcome to attend.

Please visit our event website for registration veteransdayswhs.weebly.com
or RSVP to the high school by Monday, November 4th or by calling 717-633-4807.

South Western Education Foundation
Hall of Excellence - Year 5 Inductees

It is with great pride that the South Western Education Foundation announces the names of the distinguished alumni to be inducted to the South Western Hall of Excellence. This year’s inductees are Dr. Lindsay Pfeffer (1998), William (Bill) C. Sterner (1961), and George Tracy (1965).

The induction ceremony will be held on October 26, 2019, at the Eichelberger Performing Arts Center with a social reception beginning at 3:00 p.m. and the formal awards ceremony beginning at 4:00 p.m. We hope you will consider joining us to celebrate the accomplishments of these outstanding alumni.

The monies donated to the South Western Education Foundation in honor of the inductee(s) will go directly back to fund resources for the teachers and the students of the district.

If you would like to make a contribution, kindly return the response card with your donation,
by October 11, 2019 to:

South Western Education Foundation
c/o Duane Bull – South Western School District Administration Office
225 Bowman Road
Hanover, PA 17331

CHIP covers uninsured children and teens up to age 19 – and no family earns too much to qualify. With more than 116,000 uninsured children in Pennsylvania, this is great news for families!

CHIP provides quality, comprehensive health insurance for routine doctor visits, prescriptions, dental, eye care, eyeglasses, mental health, and much more. CHIP covers uninsured kids who are not eligible for Medical Assistance. For most families, CHIP is free – for others, it is low cost.

Mrs. Nestor's second grade class won the Sumdog contest recently! The class loves playing Sumdog math games at school and at home. They are practicing the skills they need in math and are having fun doing it. Mrs. Nestor likes the easy access to reports and the ability to see the skills students are struggling with, as well as the continued student growth.

Student quotes – "I like playing the Power Boat game because after I answer math questions I can drive and go off different ramps." Another said she was struggling with math at her old school, but now she likes all the games in Sumdog. She said, "I think I'm getting better because I play the games on Sumdog to practice math."

March is "Music in our Schools" month.

We are proud to announce that Olivia Flickinger (violin) has been selected for the PMEA All-State Orchestra and Abbey Jemison (french horn) has been selected for the PMEA All-State Concert Band.

Congratulations to these two very talented musicians and to all the others who qualified to participate in the music festivals.

We are also proud of our vocalists.
On Friday, March 8, 2019 - four SWSD Choral Department students were selected to perform the National Anthem at the start of the PIAA Quarterfinals State Wrestling Tournament being held at the Giant Center in Hershey. Their performance entertained over 12,000 people that afternoon. The students were Hayden Klinedinst - Tenor; Tori Keefauver - Alto; Katie Hoster - Soprano; and Sam Jemison - Bass; posing with Mrs. Erika McKee - choral director.

post_text:
Congratulations to Mr. Jeffrey Mummert (SWSD Business Administrator) for receiving the Gary E. Reeser Memorial Award at last week's PASBO Conference - a most prestigious award!

The Gary E. Reeser Memorial Award
Each year at the PASBO annual conference, PASBO presents the Gary E. Reeser Memorial Award to an outstanding member who has exemplified professionalism, leadership and innovation in the field of school business management. In addition to the contributions and dedication to PASBO, the community service achievements of the nominees are weighed.

Mr. Brent Kessler (Central York SD - Business Manager) stated, "In my view and many others, this is the MOST prestigious award any Business Manager can ever receive in their career in School Business for the State of PA."

Mr. Mummert is standing in the center of the photo holding the plaque he received. He is joined by previous winners of the Gary E. Reeser Award.
#SWExcellence

The EHMIS Performing Arts Club will be presenting
Night at the Wax Museum on Friday, March 8 (7 PM) and Saturday, March 9 (2 PM). It is a comedy for the entire family.

School is out—but six high school students have to retake their history class in summer school. As part of a class project, the students are required to help set up the exhibits at a local wax museum. The task seems extremely boring until the unbelievable happens...the wax figures begin to come to life! Join the students on their adventure as they meet Henry VIII, Cleopatra, Blackbeard, and more.

Tickets at the door are $3 for students and $6 for adults.

Contact Ms. Nicole Shepski at EHMIS for more information. -- 717-633-4840

Good Morning, the following is an important message from the South Western School District:

Due to the forecast for deteriorating weather conditions later this afternoon, the South Western School District will be dismissing students early today, January 29th. Elementary students will be dismissed at 11:15 and secondary students will be dismissed at 12:15. Lunches will be served to the students prior to their dismissal.

All evening events are canceled.

Thank you.

post_text:
The South Western Education Foundation is sponsoring the event on March 23, 2019, at 7 PM at the Hanover Country Club. There will be live music, provided by some of our talented teachers.
You have supported the student "Taste of the Arts," and we hope you will support the Foundation through the talents of our staff and community artists and musicians.
There will be food and an opportunity for great fun, as you socialize and just hang out. Silent auction items will be available with all the monies generated going back to the teachers to provide innovative and exciting educational opportunities for their students. Some of the auction items will include: orthodontics care, a beach house weekend, dinner with the Altland House chef, fly fishing lessons, ballroom dancing lessons, family portrait sitting, and more... additional details will be forthcoming as plans are finalized.
The tickets will cost $25 and will be available through the South Western High School office and Guthrie Memorial Library, beginning in the month of February 2019.

post_text:
Student Registration

South Western School District will begin online new student registration on Monday, November 19, 2018. Once the online registration form is submitted, new student registrants and families will be contacted by the district registrar to set up an appointment. The district registrar will verify proof of residency and student age for enrollment at the registration appointment. Following the registration appointment, all new students and families will be contacted by a representative of the building(s) of enrollment to schedule a school visit.

We look forward to serving our new Mustangs within the South Western School District community by improving our enrollment process. All registration appointments must be scheduled in advance due to the changes described above.

Please see the document attached for additional registration information.
